== Prep ==

Add your boiling water to a large #saucepan{} and place on a high heat.

Pick the @rosemary{4%sprigs} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks).

Zest and then halve the @lemon{1/2%large}.

== Marinate ==

Pop the @British turkey steaks{2} on a #plate{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Sprinkle on the lemon zest and rosemary. Drizzle over a splash of @oil{}.

Rub the flavourings into the turkey.

== Cook the Turkey ==

Heat a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil!).

Brown the turkey for ~{2%minutes} on each side.

Continue to cook the turkey, turning occasionally, until no longer pink in the middle, another ~{6-8%minutes}.

When the turkey is cooked, remove from the pan, wrap loosely with #foil{} to keep warm.

== Pasta and Broccoli ==

Meanwhile, add the @chicken stock powder{1} to the boiling water and stir to dissolve. Add the @penne pasta{160%g} and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

After ~{6%minutes}, add the @broccoli florets{200%g} for the remaining ~{4%minutes}.

In the last minute, stir in the @baby spinach{125%g}, then drain in a #colander{}. Reserve a little of the stock.

== Combine ==

Return the pasta and veggies to the saucepan. Stir in the @wholegrain mustard{1%tsp}, @creme fraiche{100%g} and 2 tbsp of reserved stock.

Carefully mix and heat gently over medium heat to make sure everything is piping hot.

Mix in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

== Serve ==

Slice the turkey steak into thin strips.

Share the pasta and veggies between your plates.

Top with the turkey and a squeeze of lemon juice to finish! Enjoy!